---
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="Can You Wear Makeup in a Passport Photo? Guidelines & Tips"
  description="Wondering if you can wear makeup in a passport photo? Learn the official rules, what constitutes 'natural makeup', and how to avoid having your photo rejected."
>
  <article class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 mt-[80px] md:mt-10 mb-20">
    <nav class="mb-8" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
      <ol class="flex items-center space-x-2 text-sm text-gray-600">
        <li><a href="/" class="hover:text-primary transition-colors">Home</a></li>
        <li><span class="text-gray-400">/</span></li>
        <li><a href="/passport" class="hover:text-primary transition-colors">Passport</a></li>
        <li><span class="text-gray-400">/</span></li>
        <li class="text-gray-900">Makeup Rules</li>
      </ol>
    </nav>

    <h1 class="font-crimson text-[40px] md:text-[50px] leading-tight text-gray-900 mb-6">
      Can You Wear Makeup in a Passport Photo?
    </h1>

    <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none text-gray-700">
      <p>
        One of the most common questions applicants ask is: <strong>can you wear makeup in a passport photo?</strong> The short answer is yes, but there are strict limitations on how much and what kind of makeup is acceptable.
      </p>

      <h2 class="font-crimson text-3xl mt-10 mb-4 text-gray-900">The "Everyday Look" Rule</h2>
      <p>
        The golden rule for passport photos is that you must look like your everyday self. If you typically wear light makeup, you can wear it in your photo. However, your makeup should never alter your facial features or make you unrecognizable from your natural appearance.
      </p>

      <h2 class="font-crimson text-3xl mt-10 mb-4 text-gray-900">What to Avoid</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Contouring:</strong> Avoid heavy contouring that changes the shape of your nose, cheekbones, or jawline.</li>
        <li><strong>Gloss and Sparkle:</strong> Lip gloss, highlighter, and glitter can cause glare and reflections from the camera flash, leading to rejection. Stick to matte finishes.</li>
        <li><strong>Heavy Eyeliner/Lashes:</strong> Extremely thick eyeliner or large false eyelashes that obscure your natural eye shape should be avoided.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="font-crimson text-3xl mt-10 mb-4 text-gray-900">Tips for Success</h2>
      <p>
        Stick to a natural, matte foundation that matches your skin tone perfectly. Use neutral colors for eyeshadow and lipstick. The goal of the photo is identification, not a glamour shot. If a border agent cannot easily match your face to the photo due to heavy makeup, you will face delays at immigration.
      </p>

      <div class="mt-12 bg-blue-50 rounded-2xl p-8 text-center">
        <h3 class="font-crimson text-2xl font-bold text-blue-900 mb-4">Create your perfect passport photo</h3>
        <p class="mb-6">Upload your photo and our tool will automatically crop it to your country's required dimensions.</p>
        <a href="/passport" class="inline-block bg-primary text-white font-bold px-8 py-3 rounded-full hover:bg-primary-dark transition-colors">
          Start Now
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>
</Layout>
